<h1>Problem 977 - 2020 USA TSTST, P2 of 9, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Let \(ABC\) be a scalene triangle with incenter \(I\). The incircle of \(ABC\) touches \(\overline{BC}\), \(\overline{CA}\), \(\overline{AB}\) at points \(D\), \(E\), \(F\), respectively. Let \(P\) be the foot of the altitude from \(D\) to \(\overline{EF}\), and let \(M\) be the midpoint of \(\overline{BC}\). The rays \(AP\) and \(IP\) intersect the circumcircle of \(\triangle{ABC}\) again at points \(G\) and \(Q\), respectively. Show that the incenter of \(\triangle{GQM}\) coincides with \(D\).</p>
